                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13762116" author="daijy" created="Mon, 9 Sep 2013 19:11:17 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Would you mind a fix for all new types (Boolean, BigInteger, BigDecimal), for both JsonLoader/JsonStorer? Also need to add a test case.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13763066" author="tyro89" created="Tue, 10 Sep 2013 15:26:12 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Sure &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; I&apos;ll take a look and make this patch a full JsonLoader/JsonStorage update instead of just fixing the boolean field when storing.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13765102" author="tyro89" created="Thu, 12 Sep 2013 03:29:15 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;fixed JsonStorage/JsonLoader and added tests.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13765178" author="daijy" created="Thu, 12 Sep 2013 06:45:07 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks good. One minor comment, why not reuse TestJsonLoaderStorage?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also the final patch is bugPig-3454.patch + bugPig-3454-2.patch. Can you combine the patch?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13768511" author="tyro89" created="Mon, 16 Sep 2013 18:23:46 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s my latest patch. I&apos;ve completely updated JsonTestLoadStorage instead of adding new tests and have fixed a few things around JsonLoader and JsonStorage that surfaced thanks to the new tests. This now works pretty well &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13768512" author="tyro89" created="Mon, 16 Sep 2013 18:24:28 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Of course I meant TestJsonLoaderStorage...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13768602" author="daijy" created="Mon, 16 Sep 2013 19:43:52 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;TestJsonLoaderStorage.testJsonLoaderStorage1 is removed, is that intentional?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13768612" author="tyro89" created="Mon, 16 Sep 2013 19:51:01 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not sure what you mean by TestJsonLoaderStorage.testJsonLoaderStorage1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I removed &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;test/org/apache/pig/test/data/jsonStorage1.pig&lt;br/&gt;
test/org/apache/pig/test/data/jsonStorage1.result&lt;br/&gt;
test/org/apache/pig/test/data/jsonStorage1.schema&lt;br/&gt;
test/org/apache/pig/test/data/jsonStorage1.txt&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;since they were used by the old version of TestJsonLoaderStorage but my update version is self contained.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13768650" author="daijy" created="Mon, 16 Sep 2013 20:20:26 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I see you removed existing test in old TestJsonLoaderStorage.java: testJsonLoaderStorage1, testJsonLoaderStorage2. Usually we don&apos;t remove tests unless your new test cover all the old tests.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13768653" author="tyro89" created="Mon, 16 Sep 2013 20:23:07 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Aha yes my new tests should cover the old ones + adds test for all the new data types. I tweaked some names to make it more clear what the tests test. Feel free to make a quick sanity check in case I missed something &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13768677" author="daijy" created="Mon, 16 Sep 2013 20:43:54 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch committed to trunk. Thanks Erik!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
